# [Aloha Editor - ${project.version} - The HTML5 WYSIWYG Editor](http://aloha-editor.org/)

## Zipfile content:

* /README - This file
* /aloha - Contains the build version of aloha with all examples and plugins
* /CHANGELOG.md - The Aloha Editor Changelog
* /CHANGELOG-jquery-port.md - jQuery migration guide
* /guides - Aloha Editor Guides
* /api (Still under development)

## Security Notice

The +aloha+ folder contains some php example. Please remove example code when you plan to use the build in your project. Alternatively you can download the CDN version.

## CDN (Content Delivery Network) Locations

Cloudfront CDN:
* http://cdn.aloha-editor.org/aloha-${project.version}/lib/aloha.js
* http://cdn.aloha-editor.org/current/lib/aloha.js

JSDelivr CDN:
* http://cdn.jsdelivr.net/aloha-${project.version}/lib/aloha.js
* http://cdn.jsdelivr.net/alohaeditor/current/lib/aloha.js

## Maven

You can include Aloha Editor in your maven project using the following dependencies:

<dependency>
	<groupId>org.alohaeditor</groupId>
	<artifactId>alohaeditor</artifactId>
	<version>${project.version}</version>
	<type>zip</type>
</dependency>

<!-- The CDN Version of aloha contains no examples and no documenation --> 
<dependency>
	<groupId>org.alohaeditor</groupId>
	<artifactId>alohaeditor</artifactId>
	<version>${project.version}</version>
	<classifier>cdn</classifier>
	<type>zip</type>
</dependency>

<!-- A sourcecode snapshot of the released version -->
<dependency>
	<groupId>org.alohaeditor</groupId>
	<artifactId>alohaeditor</artifactId>
	<version>${project.version}</version>
	<classifier>source</classifier>
	<type>zip</type>
</dependency>

[Maven Archive](http://archiva.gentics.com:8081/archiva/browse/org.alohaeditor/alohaeditor)  

[Artifacts can be downloaded here](http://archiva.gentics.com:8081/archiva/repository/com.gentics.public_snapshots/org/alohaeditor/alohaeditor/${project.version}/)

## New Documentation

We're currently writing new guides. You can find these at doc/guides/output.

For help there is:
- [the wiki](https://github.com/alohaeditor/Aloha-Editor/wiki) for end-users and implementors
- [the issues tracker](https://github.com/alohaeditor/Aloha-Editor/issues) for developer support requests
- [the support forum](http://getsatisfaction.com/aloha_editor) for end-user and implementor support requests